{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NTZfSsYRpzxgpJkDmJRPEL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete understanding of the codebase. Let me analyze what needs to change.\n\n**Key Observations:**\n1. This is a **Spring Boot 3.1.0** app that already uses `jakarta.persistence.*` in entities (in `jakartaee.tutorial.roster.entity` package)\n2. The migration from \"spring\" to \"jakarta\" means migrating away from Spring Boot to a pure Jakarta EE runtime\n3. The `spring.tutorial.roster` packages use Spring-specific annotations (`@SpringBootApplication`, `@RestController`, `@Service`, etc.)\n4. The entities already use Jakarta persistence APIs\n5. There's a misnamed test file: `RequestSmokeText,java` (comma instead of dot)\n\nThe migration involves:\n- Replacing Spring Boot with a Jakarta EE application server (like Open Liberty, Payara, or WildFly)\n- Converting Spring Data JPA repositories to Jakarta Persistence (EntityManager-based)\n- Converting Spring REST controllers to JAX-RS (Jakarta REST)\n- Converting Spring DI (`@Service`, `@Autowired`) to CDI (`@Named`, `@Inject`)\n- Replacing `application.properties` with Jakarta EE configuration\n- Updating the Dockerfile to use a Jakarta EE server\n\nLet me refine the plan and start implementing:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4183,"cache_read_input_tokens":40091,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4183,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":912},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"330ba2d4-1b8a-41b4-8954-1bf20c0cd90b","uuid":"048148e8-417b-4fa9-9c8c-03d410a68b88"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01NTZfSsYRpzxgpJkDmJRPEL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01RjowVQ3RJUdPLH4seoXbMy","name":"TodoWrite","input":{"todos":[{"content":"Analyze existing codebase structure","status":"completed","activeForm":"Analyzing existing codebase structure"},{"content":"Plan migration: Spring Boot -> Jakarta EE (Open Liberty)","status":"completed","activeForm":"Planning migration strategy"},{"content":"Update parent pom.xml for Jakarta EE","status":"in_progress","activeForm":"Updating parent pom.xml"},{"content":"Update roster-common pom.xml and move packages to jakarta namespace","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating roster-common module"},{"content":"Update roster-boot pom.xml to become roster-war for Jakarta EE","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating roster-boot module"},{"content":"Convert Spring Data repositories to EntityManager-based DAOs","status":"pending","activeForm":"Converting repositories to DAOs"},{"content":"Convert Spring REST controller to JAX-RS","status":"pending","activeForm":"Converting to JAX-RS"},{"content":"Convert RequestBean from Spring @Service to CDI @Named","status":"pending","activeForm":"Converting to CDI"},{"content":"Replace RosterApplication.java with JAX-RS Application class","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating JAX-RS Application"},{"content":"Move entity imports and fix package references","status":"pending","activeForm":"Fixing entity imports"},{"content":"Create Jakarta EE config files (persistence.xml, beans.xml, server.xml)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Creating Jakarta EE config files"},{"content":"Update Dockerfile for Open Liberty","status":"pending","activeForm":"Updating Dockerfile"},{"content":"Generate smoke tests","status":"pending","activeForm":"Generating smoke tests"},{"content":"Fix misnamed test file (comma in filename)","status":"pending","activeForm":"Fixing test filename"},{"content":"B